🔄 What is a Recurring Hazard?
A hazard reported 3 or more times from the same location with the same hazard type. This means the root cause has not been fixed yet — the system automatically escalates its risk level and flags it for management review or intervention.
⏰ What is an Overdue Report?
An open hazard that has not been closed within its allowed timeframe:
🔴 Immediate = 1 day  |  🟠 High = 7 days 🟡 Medium = 30 days  |  🟢 Low = 90 days

📜 Immutable Audit Log
Every action cryptographically chained — SHA-256 hash chain, append-only, tamper-evident
🔐 Hash Chain Integrity
Each log entry contains a SHA-256 hash of its content chained to the previous entry. Any modification to past records will break the chain and be detected instantly. This log is synchronized to Firebase and cannot be edited or deleted.

📸 Google Drive Photo Upload

Paste your Google Apps Script Web App URL here to enable automatic photo uploads directly to your Google Drive folder. Once set, reporters can drag and drop photos — no manual sharing required.

📋 Setup Steps (one time only):
  1. Go to script.google.com → New Project
  2. Paste the contents of GoogleAppsScript_DriveUpload.js into the editor
  3. Click Deploy → New Deployment → Web App
  4. Set Execute as: Me · Who has access: Anyone
  5. Click Deploy → Authorize → Copy the Web App URL
  6. Paste the URL in the field above and click Test Connection

ℹ️ What are SPIs?

Safety Performance Indicators are measurable values showing whether your SMS meets its safety objectives. CAAP requires SPIs to be defined, monitored, and reviewed regularly (Section 4.8.3).

Examples: Closure rate of hazard reports, % of CAPs completed on time, number of overdue investigations.
